This Aspect is used as part of the calculations for Estimated Attainment 8 values and therefore part of the Progress 8 calculations. It will need to be populated with the KS2 Average Fine Level, expressed as a decimal, before these calculations are run in order for those measures to be generated as expected.
In 2015 and 2016 the value in this aspect should be based on English and Maths. In 2017 and 2018 this should be based on Reading and Maths. As per the DfE guidance document "Progres 8 measure in 2016 and 2017 dated March 2015",

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: understand, through the use of detailed place-based exemplars at a variety of scales, the key processes in:- physical geography relating to: geological timescales and plate tectonics; rocks, weathering and soils; weather and climate, including the change in climate from the Ice Age to the present; and glaciation, hydrology and coasts, human geography relating to: population and urbanisation; international development; economic activity in the primary, secondary, tertiary and quaternary sectors; and the use of natural resources

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Ge Human & Physical Geog Stat 79.02
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: understand how human and physical processes interact to influence, and change landscapes, environments and the climate; and how human activity relies on effective functioning of natural systems

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Ge Skills and Fieldwork Stat 79.01
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: build on their knowledge of globes, maps and atlases and apply and develop this knowledge routinely in the classroom and in the field

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Ge Skills and Fieldwork Stat 79.02
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: interpret Ordnance Survey maps in the classroom and the field, including using grid references and scale, topographical and other thematic mapping, and aerial and satellite photographs

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Ge Skills and Fieldwork Stat 79.03
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: use Geographical Information Systems (GIS) to view, analyse and interpret places and data

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Ge Skills and Fieldwork Stat 79.04
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: use fieldwork in contrasting locations to collect, analyse and draw conclusions from geographical data, using multiple sources of increasingly complex information

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Hi History Stat 79.01
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: the development of Church, state and society in Medieval Britain 1066-1509. This could include:- the Norman Conquest, Christendom, the importance of religion and the Crusades, the struggle between Church and crown, Magna Carta and the emergence of Parliament, the English campaigns to conquer Wales and Scotland up to 1314, society, economy and culture: for example, feudalism, religion in daily life (parishes, monasteries, abbeys), farming, trade and towns (especially the wool trade), art, architecture and literature, the Black Death and its social and economic impact, the Peasants' Revolt, the Hundred Years War, the Wars of the Roses; Henry VII and attempts to restore stability

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Hi History Stat 79.03
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: ideas, political power, industry and empire: Britain, 1745-1901. This could include:- the Enlightenment in Europe and Britain, with links back to 17th-Century thinkers and scientists and the founding of the Royal Society, Britain's transatlantic slave trade: its effects and its eventual abolition, the Seven Years War and The American War of Independence, the French Revolutionary wars, Britain as the first industrial nation - the impact on society, party politics, extension of the franchise and social reform, the development of the British Empire with a depth study (for example, of India), Ireland and Home Rule, Darwin's 'On The Origin of Species'

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Hi History Stat 79.02
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: the development of Church, state and society in Britain 1509-1745. This could include:- Renaissance and Reformation in Europe, the English Reformation and Counter Reformation (Henry VIII to Mary I), the Elizabethan religious settlement and conflict with Catholics (including Scotland, Spain and Ireland), the first colony in America and first contact with India, the causes and events of the civil wars throughout Britain, the Interregnum (including Cromwell in Ireland), the Restoration, 'Glorious Revolution' and power of Parliament, the Act of Union of 1707, the Hanoverian succession and the Jacobite rebellions of 1715 and 1745, society, economy and culture across the period: for example, work and leisure in town and country, religion and superstition in daily life, theatre, art, music and literature

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Hi History Stat 79.04
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: challenges for Britain, Europe and the wider world 1901 to the present day. In addition to studying the Holocaust, this could include:- women's suffrage, the First World War and the Peace Settlement, the inter-war years: the Great Depression and the rise of dictators, the Second World War and the wartime leadership of Winston Churchill, the creation of the Welfare State, Indian independence and end of Empire, social, cultural and technological change in post-war British society, Britain's place in the world since 1945

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Hi History Stat 79.05
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: a local history study:- a depth study linked to one of the British areas of study listed above, a study over time, testing how far sites in their locality reflect aspects of national history (some sites may predate 1066), a study of an aspect or site in local history dating from a period before 1066

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Hi History Stat 79.06
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: the study of an aspect or theme in British history that consolidates and extends pupils' chronological knowledge from before 1066:- the changing nature of political power in Britain, traced through selective case studies from the Iron Age to the present, Britain's changing landscape from the Iron Age to the present, a study of an aspect of social history, such as the impact through time of the migration of people to, from and within the British Isles, a study in depth into a significant turning point: for example, the Neolithic Revolution

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Hi History Stat 79.07
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: at least one study of a significant society or issue in world history and its interconnections with other world developments [for example, Mughal India 1526-1857; China's Qing dynasty 1644-1911; Changing Russian empires c1800-1989; USA in the 20th Century]

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Grammar & Vocabulary Stat 79.01
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: identify and use tenses or other structures which convey the present, past, and future as appropriate to the language being studied

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Grammar & Vocabulary Stat 79.02
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: use and manipulate a variety of key grammatical structures and patterns, including voices and moods, as appropriate

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Grammar & Vocabulary Stat 79.03
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: develop and use a wide-ranging and deepening vocabulary that goes beyond their immediate needs and interests, allowing them to give and justify opinions and take part in discussion about wider issues

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Linguistic Competence Stat 79.01
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: listen to a variety of forms of spoken language to obtain information and respond appropriately

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Linguistic Competence Stat 79.02
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: transcribe words and short sentences that they hear with increasing accuracy

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Linguistic Competence Stat 79.03
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: initiate and develop conversations, coping with unfamiliar language and unexpected responses, making use of important social conventions such as formal modes of address

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Linguistic Competence Stat 79.04
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: express and develop ideas clearly and with increasing accuracy, both orally and in writing

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Linguistic Competence Stat 79.05
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: speak coherently and confidently, with increasingly accurate pronunciation and intonation

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Linguistic Competence Stat 79.06
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: read and show comprehension of original and adapted materials from a range of different sources, understanding the purpose, important ideas and details, and provide an accurate English translation of short, suitable material

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Linguistic Competence Stat 79.07
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: read literary texts in the language [such as stories, songs, poems and letters], to stimulate ideas, develop creative expression and expand understanding of the language and culture

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS MFL Linguistic Competence Stat 79.08
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: write prose using an increasingly wide range of grammar and vocabulary, write creatively to express their own ideas and opinions, and translate short written text accurately into the foreign language

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Mu Music Stat 79.01
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: play and perform confidently in a range of solo and ensemble contexts using their voice, playing instruments musically, fluently and with accuracy and expression

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Mu Music Stat 79.02
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: improvise and compose; and extend and develop musical ideas by drawing on a range of musical structures, styles, genres and traditions

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Mu Music Stat 79.03
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: use staff and other relevant notations appropriately and accurately in a range of musical styles, genres and traditions

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Mu Music Stat 79.04
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: identify and use the inter-related dimensions of music expressively and with increasing sophistication, including use of tonalities, different types of scales and other musical devices

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS Mu Music Stat 79.06
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: develop a deepening understanding of the music that they perform and to which they listen, and its history

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS PE PE Stat 79.01
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: use a range of tactics and strategies to overcome opponents in direct competition through team and individual games [for example, badminton, basketball, cricket, football, hockey, netball, rounders, rugby and tennis]

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS PE PE Stat 79.02
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: develop their technique and improve their performance in other competitive sports [for example, athletics and gymnastics]

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS PE PE Stat 79.03
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: perform dances using advanced dance techniques within a range of dance styles and forms

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS PE PE Stat 79.04
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: take part in outdoor and adventurous activities which present intellectual and physical challenges and be encouraged to work in a team, building on trust and developing skills to solve problems, either individually or as a group

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS PE PE Stat 79.05
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: analyse their performances compared to previous ones and demonstrate improvement to achieve their personal best

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: CAS PE PE Stat 79.06
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: take part in competitive sports and activities outside school through community links or sports clubs

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'he was upset because it says "he was crying"'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg how a character is feeling, what makes a plant grow.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF4L6b Identify, Comment
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg how the writer builds up to an unexpected ending, juxtaposes ideas, changes perspectives or uses everyday examples to illustrate complex ideas.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF4L5a Identify, Comment
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'it tells you all things burglars can do to your house and then the last section explains how the alarm protects you'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF4L5b Identify, Comment
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'each section starts with a question as if he's answering the crowd'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'he describes the accident first and then goes back to tell you why the child was in the road'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF4L4b Identify, Comment
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'the writer uses bullet points for the main reasons'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF4L3a Identify, Comment
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'it tells about all the different things you can do at the zoo'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF5L4b Explain, Comment Lang
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg "'disgraceful" is a good word to use to show he is upset'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF5L3a Explain, Comment Lang
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'there are lots of adjectives'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF5L6a Explain, Comment Lang
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg tracing an image; identifying and commenting on patterns or structure in the use of language; or recognising changes in language use at different points in a text.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF5L6b Explain, Comment Lang
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'all the images of flowers make the events seem less horrific and makes it even sadder'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF5L5a Explain, Comment Lang
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'when it gets to the climax they speak in short sentences and quickly which makes it more tense'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF5L5b Explain, Comment Lang
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg '"inked up" is a good way of describing how the blackberries go a bluey black colour as they ripen'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF6L6a Explain, Comment View
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg commenting on repetition of 'Brutus was an honourable man'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF6L6b Explain, Comment View
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'you know it's told from Eric's point of view even though he doesn't use the first person'

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF6L6c Explain, Comment View
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'when Macduff just says he has no children you hate Macbeth because you remember the scene in the castle. You realise Macduff's revenge can never be complete'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'the writer is strongly against war and wants to persuade the reader to agree'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF6L5b Explain, Comment View
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'at the end he knows he's done wrong and makes the snake sound attractive and mysterious'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF6L5c Explain, Comment View
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'you'd be persuaded to sign up because 25p a week doesn't seem that much to help someone see'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF6L4a Explain, Comment View
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'it's all about why going to the dentist is important and how you should look after your teeth'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Name: APP Re AF6L4b Explain, Comment View
AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'he only tells you good things about the farm and makes the shop sound boring'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'the way she describes him as "ratlike" and "shifty" makes you think he's disgusting'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'the writer doesn't like violence'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'she was just horrible like my nan is sometimes'.

AssessmentResultComponent.Description: eg 'it tells you how to do something', 'she thinks it's not fair'.
